         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Replacing the mixing arm bearings:</b>
            </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">The mixing arm bearings (1) are bushings that are inserted into the drilled holes of the rotor, and into which the mixing arms are inserted.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">The mixing arm bearings can only be replaced after the mixing arms have been
                     removed.</li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_ip2_f1s_lcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_jp2_f1s_lcc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <table id="table_gbd_g1s_lcc" class="- topic/table ">
                           <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                              <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                              <colspec colname="c2"
                                       colnum="2"
                                       colwidth="1.47*"
                                       class="- topic/colspec "/>
                              <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                                 <row class="- topic/row ">
                                    <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">1</p>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">Mixingarm bearing</p>
                                    </entry>
                                 </row>
                                 <row class="- topic/row ">
                                    <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">2</p>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">Mixing armscraper</p>
                                    </entry>
                                 </row>
                              </tbody>
                           </tgroup>
                        </table>
                     </p>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Replacing the mixing arm scrapers:</b>
            </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">The scraper (2) is a sealing ring that is inserted into the same drilled hole in the rotor into which the mixing arm is inserted.  (See image in step 3 above.)</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">The scrapers can only be replaced after the mixing arms have been removed.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Replacing the mixing paddles:</b>
            </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Undo the screws (1), and remove the paddles (2).</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Before installing the new mixing paddles, soak an intermediate textile or
                     paper gasket layer (3) in water.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Place the paper layer between the mounting part and the mixing paddle.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Ensure that the mixing paddles (2) are attached so that their top edge
                     overlaps the mounting part.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Readjust the paddle height using the slotted holes.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Before tightening up the fastening screws, make sure that there is a parallel
                     gap between the bottom of the paddle and the trough floor wear liner (1-2 mm,
                     or 0.04 to 0.08 inch).</li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" id="note_z5w_s1s_lcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Re-tighten theconnection between the mixing paddles and the scraper paddles
                     after five hours of operating time.</p>
               </note>
               <note type="note" id="note_avw_s1s_lcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Inspect all mixing paddles at regular interval s for wear and damage. Replace
                     if necessary. Using worn or damaged paddles can lead to serious damage to the
                     mixer.</p>
               </note>
